*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-æŋ|-æŋ]]

===Etymology 1===
From Old Norse ''fang'' ‘capture, embrace’, from a Germanic base ''*fanga-'' (source also of Old English [[fon|fōn]]).

====Noun====
'''fang''' (''plural'' '''fangs''')

#A long, pointed [[canine tooth]] used for biting and tearing [[flesh]] or (in snakes) for [[inject]]ing [[venom]].

